Apr 27 2009 	Unbeatable value	We stayed for just one night in April of 2009, and the Chelsea Savoy had no problem taking a booking for Saturday night only, which not many other hotels were willing to do. A lot of the other reviews here mentioned poor service, but the two people working at the desk Saturday afternoon welcomed us as soon as we walked in and we very cordial and polite the whole time we were there. The rooms still have that funky &quot;just painted&quot; smell, but after a few minutes, you don't notice it at all. The bathroom was big (as others mentioned) for New York City standards. The room and bathroom were both very clean. The hotel literally sits on top of the 1 and 9 line's 23rd st. subway station and is a block away (east) from the B/D/F/V or (west) A/C/E subway lines so you can be practically anywhere in Manhattan within 20 mins or so. We were on the second floor and still had no problems sleeping with the street noise, but others might notice it. As others have mentioned, the breakfast is nothing special, just pastries and coffee/tea. There is no restaurant at the hotel (as of 4/2009), but there are about 3 or 4 decently priced diners within a block in either direction, so it's no big deal. The hotel was more than happy to keep our bag for the afternoon after we checked out.The deal maker for this hotel is the price. We paid $125 for a queen bed on a Saturday night - extremely low by Manhattan standards and an incredible value for the money! We will be back to the Savoy on our next trip to NYC.	
